The paper deals with Fourier analysis of Boolean functions, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and theoretical computer science (cs.CC). The concept of sparsity is also relevant in the areas of data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses an application to testing Booleanity, which falls under the category of property testing (cs.DM).
